- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with algorithms and implementations for isolating real roots of polynomials, which is a common problem in symbolic computation.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity and implementation of numerical algorithms for root isolation.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper presents algorithmic and complexity results for root isolation.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possible category as root isolation is a fundamental problem in computational geometry.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the implementation of the algorithms in the core library of Mathematica, which is a system for symbolic computation and control.
